1 2. Bulk purchases prohibited. The bulk purchase of tickets or shares for a lottery
2 game is prohibited.
3 3. Refusal of payment. The commission may refuse payment of a prize for a winning
4 ticket or share that was purchased as part of a bulk purchase in violation of subsection 2.
5 SUMMARY
66 This bill prohibits a person or group of persons working together from making bulk
77 purchases of lottery tickets or shares. The bill provides that the term "bulk purchase" means
88 the purchase, in aggregate, of tickets or shares in a lottery game in an amount exceeding
99 $100,000. The bill provides that the State Liquor and Lottery Commission may refuse
1100 payment of a prize for a winning ticket or share that was purchased as part of a bulk
1111 purchase. The bill requires the commission to adopt rules related to bulk purchasing. The
1122 bill also authorizes the Director of Alcoholic Beverages and Lottery Operations within the
1133 Department of Administrative and Financial Services to suspend or revoke a person's
1144 license to sell lottery tickets if the person knowingly sells tickets or shares to a person
1155 attempting to make a bulk purchase. These provisions do not apply to the Tri-state Lotto
1166 Compact.
